text: The Governor of Chaco () is the figure that holds the executive power of the Chaco Province, Argentina, and the highest political office of the province. ==Governors since 1983== Governor Term in office Party Election Vice Governor Florencio Tenev – PJ 1983 Alberto Torresagasti Danilo Baroni – PJ 1987 Emilio Carrara Rolando Tauguinas – ACHA 1991 Luis Varisco Ángel Rozas – UCR 1995 Miguel Pibernus 1999 Roy Nikisch Roy Nikisch – UCR 2003 Eduardo Aníbal Moro Jorge Capitanich – PJ 2007 Juan Carlos Bacileff Ivanoff 2011 Juan Carlos Bacileff Ivanoff – PJ Vacant Jorge Capitanich – PJ Juan Carlos Bacileff Ivanoff :Domingo Peppo – PJ 2015 Daniel Capitanich Jorge Capitanich – PJ 2019 Analía Rach Quiroga == References == Category:Politics of Argentina Category:Argentina-related lists Category:Chaco Province
